ge of Application: Rigid cellular Polyiso roof insulation board is the most
ely used insulating material for above-deck commercial roof construction
orth America. In commercial roofing assemblies, one or more layers of
iso are placed above the roof deck (typically steel, concrete, or wood) and
eath the roofing membrane. The Polyiso boards may be attached to the
deck with various mechanical fasteners and construction adhesives or
d in place with ballast stones or concrete pavers placed above the roofing
mbrane. The roofing membrane also may be mechanically attached through
Polyiso insulation, adhered to the top Polyiso facer or held in place with
ast. Additional common elements of this construction may include air
rders, vapor barriers, and thermal barriers placed beneath the Polyiso
lation and cover boards placed between the Polyiso insulation and the
fing membrane. A typical above-deck roofing assembly using Polyiso is
trated in Figure 3.
